  "phenotype_node": "Shoot_Branching",
  "biology_prose": "Shoot branching is regulated by a hormonal cascade where auxin inhibits cytokinin, promoting apical dominance. Strigolactone, synthesized via the MAX pathway (MAX3, MAX4, MAX1), signals through D14 and MAX2 to degrade SMXL678 proteins, which otherwise suppress BRC1. BRC1, a key integrator, inhibits shoot branching when expressed, and its repression by SMXL678 links strigolactone signaling to bud inhibition. Decapitation removes the auxin source, reducing strigolactone biosynthesis, stabilizing SMXL678, repressing BRC1, and thereby releasing buds for outgrowth.",
